keyFacts: The document is a detailed witness coordination schedule for a legal proceeding, spanning from late November to mid-December.
Specific instructions are given to prevent witnesses from staying at the same hotels, indicating concerns about witness contact or collusion.
Witnesses include a Mar-a-Lago custodian and a sergeant from the Palm Beach Police Department, linking the proceeding to locations and personnel associated with the Epstein case.
FBI personnel from New York are scheduled to participate remotely, suggesting federal involvement in the proceeding.
The schedule includes various records custodians (birth certificate, AT&T, FedEx, school district), indicating a focus on documentary evidence collection.
